Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
69660c0c-bd74-49f3-b425-3ee31e72a456.ceac066d-5249-4c33-bc1f-a0dbc53402eb.description=
Checks if a number or word is greater than or equal to another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - the first value.
value2 - the second value.

Returns\:
value1 <\= value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
69660c0c-bd74-49f3-b425-3ee31e72a456.description=
Scan opened ports on give host  

Inputs\: 
 host - IP address Host name to be scanned
 lowestPort - lowest port range
 highestPort - highest port range
 portType - the type of ports to be scanned (TCP or UDP). If not specified, the TCP ports are scanned.

Note\:
 To scan specific port give same port as parameter for both Lowest Port and Highest Port, 

Responses\:
 success - the command was executed successfully
 failure - the command could not be executed

Result\:
 finalResult - Information about the ports' statuses on a given machine.

Extra results\:
 host - the IP of the host for which the ports are scanned
 ports - Number of ports scanned
 opened - Number of ports open
 closed - Number of ports closed
 dropped - Number of ports dropped
